## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="cb37e-102">Questa enumerazione viene utilizzata come argomento a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.RecognizeAsync%28System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizeMode%29>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="cb37e-102">This enumeration is used as an argument to <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.RecognizeAsync%28System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizeMode%29>.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="cb37e-103">Nell'esempio seguente viene illustrata l'implementazione di un pulsante di avvio/arresto di un'applicazione che dispone di un'interfaccia utente grafica e Usa <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="cb37e-103">The following example shows the implementation of a start/stop button for an application that has a graphical user interface and uses <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="cb37e-104">A seconda dello stato dell'applicazione, <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.RecognizeAsync%28System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizeMode%29> viene chiamato con uno o più quando si fa clic sul pulsante.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="cb37e-104">Depending on the state of the application, <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.RecognizeAsync%28System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizeMode%29> is called with either Single or Multiple when the button is clicked.</span></span>  
  
```  
private void _startRecogButton_Click(object sender, EventArgs eventArgs)   
{  
  
  // Toggle speech recognition on.  
  if (_startRecogButton.Text == "Start Speech Recognition")   
  {       
    _startRecogButton.Text = "Stop Speech Recognition";  
    if (_useMultiple)   
    {  
      _recognitionEngine.RecognizeAsync(RecognizeMode.Multiple);  
    }   
    else   
    {  
      _recognitionEngine.RecognizeAsync(RecognizeMode.Single);  
    }  
  }  
  
  // Toggle speech recognition off.   
  else   
  {                                                        
    _startRecogButton.Text = "Start Speech Recognition";  
  
    // Stop after current phrase is finished.  
    if (_friendlyStop)   
    {       
      _recognitionEngine.RecognizeAsyncStop();   
    }  
  
    // Stop before current phrase is finished.  
    else   
    {        
      _recognitionEngine.RecognizeAsyncCancel();   
    }  
  }  
}  
```
